All validations are based on the "Search Engine Optimization Starter Guide" document from Google http://tinyurl.com/yjm24yq check the project page for a full list of validations.

      SEO checker allows you to preview the Google search result snippet when editing content  and will give feedback about keyword usage in content and met information

      SEO checker will report any inbound link that is broken and will automatically redirect to the correct page when a link pointing to your website uses the wrong extension, php instead of aspx for example and will automatically redirect to the correct page when an editor renames or moves a document.

      SEO checker allows you to generate meta data based on existing content on the page, can automatically generate robot.txt and sitemap.xml files for you.

      SEO checker will also automatically solve canonical issues using its own URL Rewrite module.

A framework for building large scalable distributed applications with ease
summary:
A framework for building large scalable distributed applications with ease.
      Main components:
      Stardust.Nucleus:
      the stardust IOC container.
      This is a lightweight IOC containter that supports dependency injection and Object Lifecycle Management with an emphasis on performance.

      Stardust.Interstellar:
      the stardust service and configuration framework.
      Provides support for centralized configuration and a unified programming model for integration technologies. Any service/integration technology has the same activation/usage providing an implementation agnostic abstraction. This also eases unit testing by allowing easy mocking of the service clients.

      Stardust.Wormhole:
      The stardust type mapping framework.
      Stardust ships with a light weight type mapping and data merge tool.
